The Judicial Service Commission (JSC) has announced the shortlisted candidates for its next round of interviews in April. In November, the JSC published notices in the media to fill vacancies in various superior courts with the closing date set for 8 December. The JSC met on 29 January to compile a list of candidates, to be interviewed at a sitting in Midrand from 9 to 13 April. In total, the JSC has listed 25 candidates to fill posts in the Supreme Court of Appeal, Competition Appeal Court, Electoral Court, Free State division of the High Court and the KwaZulu-Natal division of the High Court. Candidates will be notified of the date, time and venue in due course. To view the full list of candidates, click here. -TNA Reporter